Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.94,0:00:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, it's past your bedtime. Go take your bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.07,0:00:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a little more! It's just getting good!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.78,0:01:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have swim practice tomorrow, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.99,0:01:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:01:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you? Mr. Dracula?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:01:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.05,0:02:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a simple wizard resting his tired wings after flying for so long...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.89,0:02:08.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.53,0:02:16.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There he is! That's him!\NDon't let him escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.94,0:02:19.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Catch the Kaito Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.99,0:02:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you, Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.63,0:02:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? You saw the Kaito Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.43,0:02:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious, Ayumi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! He was so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He really is the modern-day Arsene Lupin!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what is the modern-day\NHolmes going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.10,0:02:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid! I'm gonna catch him someday, obviously!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:21.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm high school detective Kudo Shin'ichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.68,0:03:25.51,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I went with old friend and classmate,\NMouri Ran, to an amusement park
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.51,0:03:29.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}where I witnessed a suspicious deal with a man dressed in black!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:32.10,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I was so absorbed with watching the deal
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:35.31,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}that I didn't notice a second man sneak up from behind me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:41.78,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He forced me to take a poison, and when I woke up...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.78,0:03:45.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...my body had shrunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:49.08,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If they learned Kudo Shin'ichi was alive, they might go after me again,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.08,0:03:52.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}putting all the people around me in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.12,0:03:55.42,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Per Dr. Agasa's advice,\NI decided to conceal my identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.42,0:03:59.80,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When Ran asked my name,\NI quickly answered, "Edogawa Conan."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.55,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To get information on the men,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:05.14,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wound up living with Ran and her detective father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.06,0:04:13.19,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm the great detective, Mouri Kogoro...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:22.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's known as "Sleeping Kogoro."\NThis is because...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:25.07,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...I put him to sleep with my stun-gun wristwatch
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.07,0:04:30.74,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and use my voice-changing bowtie to solve cases with his voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.74,0:04:34.50,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}These two gadgets are Dr. Agasa's inventions!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.50,0:04:37.08,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Despite how it seems, he's a real genius,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.08,0:04:41.09,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and he's always making me new, unique gadgets,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:44.09,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}such as a Turbo-Engine\NSkateboard, Tracking Glasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.09,0:04:47.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and Power-Assisted Kick Shoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:51.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In particular, he upgraded the skateboard
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:55.94,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so it can run for 30 minutes at night if it's charged during the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.10,0:05:03.11,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there are two others besides the doc who know my true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.11,0:05:06.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hattori Heiji, high school detective from the west,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.45,0:05:09.41,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and Haibara Ai, a transfer student.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.41,0:05:14.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She originally worked with the men in black, but to escape from them,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:18.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}she took the same poison I did and shrank!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.17,0:05:22.76,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While following their organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:26.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I stand up to difficult cases that happen one after the other!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:30.55,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And now... a new rival has appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.72,0:05:34.56,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I find the ray of light in the darkness of confusion and suspicion!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:38.19,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Even when I'm small, my mind remains that of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:40.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There is always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:43.78,Signs,,0,0,0,,Metro Police
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.45,0:05:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaito #1412, AKA "Kaito Kid," has struck 134 times thus far!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.16,0:05:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,15 of those have been overseas, in 12 different countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,including America, France, and Germany!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.71,0:06:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,152 jewels have been stolen in all!\NTotal loss of 38,725,000,000 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, a new warning letter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.68,0:06:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,arrived from the Kaito Kid yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"When time moves from the twilight of Leo to the daybreak of Virgo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.68,0:06:21.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When a clock with no second hand inscribes the 12th letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.94,0:06:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at a tall building shining in the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall appear and take the Memories Egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.78,0:06:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the Last Wizard of the Century, Kaito Kid."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.86,0:06:32.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaito Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.57,0:06:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Memories Egg" in the letter refers to an Imperial Easter Egg,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.29,0:06:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a treasure of the Romanov\NDynasty, found last month
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.29,0:06:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in the Suzuki Zaibatsu's storehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Easter Eggs are eggs made by the jeweler Fabergé,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as Easter presents for the\NRussian empress, from the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fifty were made between 1885 and 1916.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.52,0:07:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this newly-discovered egg is the 51st.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.15,0:07:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Suzuki Zaibatsu will be putting the 51st egg on display August 23,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.19,0:07:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at the new Suzuki Modern Art\NGallery in the Osaka Castle Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, as for the coded message... Nakamori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.58,0:07:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, "...Moves from the twilight of Leo to the daybreak of Virgo."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:28.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This refers to the evening of\NAugust 22, the last day of Leo,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the dawn of August 23, the first day of Virgo,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.30,0:07:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and indicates the date of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.84,0:07:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next is, "When a clock with no second hand inscribes the 12th letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's believed this indicates the time of the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.19,0:07:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it has yet to be deciphered!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.44,0:07:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lastly is, "A tall building shining in the heavens."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.02,0:07:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a castle tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.65,0:07:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It indicates the Kaito Kid will appear at Osaka Castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.41,0:07:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, this letter says,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.24,0:08:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Between the evening of August 22 and the dawn of August 23,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will appear at the tower of Osaka Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.96,0:08:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and steal the Imperial Easter Egg!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.59,0:08:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We will be investigating in collaboration with the Osaka police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, Mr. Suzuki has personally asked for the help
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:20.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of the private detective, Mr. Mouri Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.31,0:08:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our objective here is to keep the egg safe at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.77,0:08:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if it means letting him get away, we must keep the egg safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:39.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't give me that wimpiness!\NThe egg comes second! Got it, men?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.95,0:08:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For our pride and dignity,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we police must throw that snobby sneak-thief into a freezing jail cell!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.76,0:08:58.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I think I just accepted one hell of a job...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:11.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran! Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.86,0:09:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! A limousine, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.45,0:09:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the Suzuki Zaibatsu for ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.54,0:09:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today is a special day, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.33,0:09:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Special?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gotta be posh if I'm meeting my beloved Kaito Kid{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} today!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.42,0:09:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so silly, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.01,0:09:35.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Beloved Kid{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-sama{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! Our driver is\NNishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Daddy's secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.39,0:09:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's traveled all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.31,0:09:48.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he speaks English,\NFrench, and German fluently!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.94,0:09:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not fair, Doc!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan went to Osaka all by himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.57,0:10:00.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to see the Kid again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.99,0:10:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Running off all by himself is his specialty!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now. Don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, have some watermelon and cool your anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.63,0:10:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.84,0:10:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Thank you for the food!\N- Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.63,0:10:17.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can eat after you've solved my riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.67,0:10:19.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious, Doc!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.47,0:10:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.43,0:10:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're children. I can't give you the impression it's easy to get things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.98,0:10:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I [washi] have many grandkids [ooku no mago]. How old am I?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.73,0:10:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa! You have grandkids, Doc?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a riddle!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.36,0:10:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's no use without Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.08,0:10:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happens to this watermelon, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.62,0:10:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.66,0:10:49.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're still an egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.92,0:10:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Washi" can also mean "eagle."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.79,0:10:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ooku no mago" can be changed to "tamago." [egg]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.38,0:10:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you're zero years old if you're in an egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:11:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Absolutely correct! Well done, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!\NI knew you could solve it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is...\N...amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara's part of our Junior\NDetective League, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.89,0:11:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.10,0:11:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.74,0:11:26.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now let's see how you handle that other egg, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-kun{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.66,0:12:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're really being cautious...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:14.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I doubt even an ant could crawl though unnoticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But of course! We are dealing with Kaito Kid{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} here! He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.25,0:12:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...an elusive, ever-changing, gentleman thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.67,0:12:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He easily breaks through tough security and safes with his magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,plus he can completely alter his face, voice, and personality as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One thing's for sure: That's one heck of an enemy you've made...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.57,0:12:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.07,0:12:42.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.28,0:12:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Him again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.07,0:12:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh! Why do you always call Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} "Kudo"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.20,0:12:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My bad! It's just that his eyes remind me of Kudo's, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I always call him that, on accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:12:58.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:13:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You kept saying all morning that\NKudo's coming, Kudo's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.47,0:13:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you should probably see a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is he Hattori Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, the high school detective of the west?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.43,0:13:14.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a real stud!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't even try! He and\NKazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} grew up together!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.69,0:13:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're bickering like that now, but they're really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I can tell.\NThey're just like you and Shin'ichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.62,0:13:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only I had a boy I grew up with, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.34,0:13:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, hello there, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.35,0:13:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming all this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.18,0:13:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.85,0:13:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for coming, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.19,0:14:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Sonoko. Who might these two be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.27,0:14:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and\NToyama Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.65,0:14:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is known as the "high school detective of the west."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's famous in the Kansai area!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:14.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's quite something! I'm depending on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! You can count on me, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.71,0:14:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you! Don't call the chairman of the Suzuki Zaibatsu "old man"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NAnyway, let me introduce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.63,0:14:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Sergei Ovchinnikov{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.42,0:14:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1st Secretary of the Russian Embassy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.63,0:14:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.97,0:14:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next to him is the fine art dealer, Inui Shouichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.68,0:14:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who is already asking to purchase it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.52,0:14:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's Hoshi Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.69,0:14:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a researcher of the Romanov Dynasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:43.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ni hao.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.69,0:14:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is Sagawa Ryu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the freelance cameraman and writer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.78,0:14:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've hired to film and document the egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.03,0:14:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiya!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.53,0:14:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... purchase? For what sort of price?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.91,0:14:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,800 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.33,0:14:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-Eight hundred million?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can pay more, if you'll let me have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.63,0:15:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chairman! The Imperial Easter Eggs originally belonged to Russia!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.55,0:15:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't sell yours to this sleazy broker!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.84,0:15:13.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please donate it to one of Russia's museums!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who're you calling sleazy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.31,0:15:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.77,0:15:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Filming you people might be more fun than filming the egg itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.90,0:15:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're acting like you don't care, but if you're a Romanov researcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.98,0:15:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,shouldn't you desperately want the egg for yourself, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.66,0:15:37.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... But I can't compete with 800 million...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.66,0:15:41.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, huh? 200 million is the most I could scrounge up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.96,0:15:47.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, now. The Kid's not the only one after the egg! They all are...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.92,0:15:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, we can save discussion about the egg for a later day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.93,0:15:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.13,0:15:57.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well. I suppose I'll leave for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.20,0:16:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chairman! I've brought the egg!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.74,0:16:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you. Put it on the table, if you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.95,0:16:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.54,0:16:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! He's going to show us the egg!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's nothing that fancy on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, I unknowingly played with it as a toy when I was little!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.80,0:16:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A toy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.69,0:16:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is an Imperial Easter Egg?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.81,0:16:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, could you get us some cold drinks?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno, it's less exciting than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.86,0:16:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's like an ostrich egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.57,0:16:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It opens up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.08,0:17:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! I'm impressed you knew!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside is a solid gold model of Emperor Nicholai's family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.09,0:17:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's really somethin'
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.25,0:17:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This egg does something interesting, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa! This thing's cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Fabergé's old notes was the design for the inside of this egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.23,0:17:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what proved it was a legitimate egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.91,0:17:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is "Memories Egg" the English translation of its Russian name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.95,0:17:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.66,0:17:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Russian, it's "vospominaniya," or "memories."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say. How is flipping through a book a memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot! The emperor reading a book to his kids is the memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.59,0:18:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are those jewels shining underneath the egg's lid?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.01,0:18:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's only glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.48,0:18:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it's a present from the emperor to the empress?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.65,0:18:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.61,0:18:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, Russia was in financial trouble when the 51st was made.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.74,0:18:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the Kid's letter is what seems strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.83,0:18:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"A tall building shining in the heavens."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.12,0:18:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would Osaka Castle shine?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.04,0:18:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You dummy. The retired emperor who built Osaka Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,built it as the foundation for all of Osaka's development!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.21,0:18:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's like the light of Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.51,0:18:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.55,0:18:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kid will appear in Osaka\NCastle's tower! No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.97,0:18:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.10,0:18:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"When a clock with no second hand inscribes the 12th letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.06,0:18:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just can't figure out what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be the 12th letter in the Japanese alphabet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The 12th letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.90,0:19:00.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shi"? Could it mean 4 o'clock, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's too simple for one of the Kid's codes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've figured it out, Superintendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not the Japanese alphabet, but the English alphabet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.29,0:19:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The English alphabet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The 12th letter in the English alphabet is L! In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.72,0:19:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...3 o'clock?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Impressive, great detective! Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's gotta be it! 3:00 a.m. Is before sunrise
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and matches perfectly with "dawn of Virgo"!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.48,0:19:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just you wait, Kaito Kid!\NWe'll get you this time, for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.07,0:19:43.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got "great luck"!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.49,0:19:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.16,0:19:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Waiting: You will reunite with the person you love."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.00,0:19:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that mean Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Eh?\N- Oh! Good for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.08,0:19:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Introduce him to me sometime!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.34,0:19:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.92,0:20:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, then! The question is how we pass the time until 3:00 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.38,0:20:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For now, I guess we should eat...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.02,0:20:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, show those two around, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.02,0:20:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.10,0:20:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna show this runt around the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.48,0:20:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come? Come on, let's go together!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.44,0:20:23.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just how men are sometimes.\NRight, C-C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.11,0:20:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're gonna fix that soon, I hope?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.62,0:20:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? What's with the attitude?\NI can tell 'em the truth, if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Please assist me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's more like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't forget to smile when asking people for something!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.09,0:20:38.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You jerk...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's strange seeing those two get along...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.80,0:20:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, who cares! We can have a girls' day out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's find some hot Osaka men and have them pay for our meals!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.98,0:20:56.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, let's check out Pick-Up Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.65,0:21:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're thinkin' about that 12th letter thing, aren't ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.19,0:21:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I know what "L" is in the Russian alphabet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.03,0:21:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Russian alphabet?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.99,0:21:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Russian "L" is the English "K."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.08,0:21:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, clock hands can't make a "K" shape...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.08,0:21:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, the "Last Wizard of the Century" at the end of the letter bugs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.08,0:21:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's such a snob.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's never called himself that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.63,0:21:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, the Kid's only ever gone after jewels. So why the egg now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.14,0:21:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyways, what fortune did you get earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.10,0:21:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't looked at that stupid thing yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.15,0:21:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not? It's gonna tell you how your duel with the Kid goes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:43.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.90,0:21:49.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,"Some Luck"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.11,0:21:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? "Some luck," huh?\NThat's a pretty vague fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no telling if you'll win or lose your duel with the Kid now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:21:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The one you wait for will come"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.17,0:22:03.13,Signs,,0,0,0,,"Travel: Your secret will come to light. Avoid traveling."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.13,0:22:04.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.71,0:22:06.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.68,0:22:09.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.47,0:22:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fortunes here are right a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.06,0:22:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.14,0:22:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.98,0:22:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A traditional Japanese restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.77,0:22:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. We now know the Kid will appear at 3:00 tomorrow morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.32,0:22:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so what do you say until then?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.57,0:22:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds great to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.28,0:22:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chairman! It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.86,0:22:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes! I appreciate your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.33,0:22:36.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Are you moving it to the exhibition room?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.20,0:22:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- The fake will go there.\N- Fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.92,0:22:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All previous times, we naively left the Kid's prey where he indicated
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.54,0:22:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in his warning letters, and he swiped it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.67,0:22:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time, we're making it so he doesn't know where the real one is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.18,0:22:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good thinking! So, where will it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.76,0:23:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I can't tell you!\NOnly my two men and I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.40,0:23:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.19,0:23:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...I've already made sure they're not the Kid in disguise!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.49,0:23:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.70,0:23:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a chance that you're the Kid, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.70,0:23:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I better make sure you're not the Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.43,0:23:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Kosaka Natsumi.\NThis is my butler, Sawabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.23,0:23:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd very much like to meet the chairman
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.15,0:23:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in regards to the Imperial\NEaster Egg in this pamphlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.15,0:23:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. The chairman is out at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.24,0:23:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can speak with you, if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.41,0:23:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The egg in this photo is different
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.45,0:23:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from the picture my great-grandfather left!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.12,0:24:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! That's neat! If 3:00 a.m. Is an "L," right now's a Japanese "he"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.17,0:24:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"He"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.38,0:24:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 7:13 right now.\NAt 7:20 will be a perfect "he"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.84,0:24:18.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The 12th Japanese letter in that twilight and dawn line is a "he"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.39,0:24:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori! The Kid didn't mean 3:00 AM! He meant 7:20 PM!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.48,0:24:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say what?! Hey! Where are you going, Kudo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.36,0:24:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Osaka Castle! You guard the egg!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.90,0:24:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rain? The weather forecast said it'd be clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.61,0:24:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.37,0:24:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "tall building" isn't the castle tower!\NIt's the Tsutenkaku Tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.41,0:24:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tsutenkaku?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.29,0:24:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A weather forecast shines at the top of the Tsutenkaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.25,0:24:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.26,0:25:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.40,0:25:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! Let the show begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.45,0:25:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.17,0:25:31.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, fireworks!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.75,0:25:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Truly a summer tradition!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.52,0:25:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.10,0:25:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even Osaka's fireworks are flashy!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.10,0:25:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange. Today's not a fireworks day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.78,0:25:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector! Fireworks are being launched over by Osaka Castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.86,0:26:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An incredible amount, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.49,0:26:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down! That's not the Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.16,0:26:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still have over 7 hours until the time he specified.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.42,0:26:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I doubt he'll ever suspect that the egg is being hidden
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.38,0:26:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in a warehouse-like place such as this!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.46,0:26:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori! Which way is the Tsutenkaku?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.59,0:26:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.01,0:26:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't any fireworks over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.93,0:26:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fireworks at Osaka Castle are to take all eyes off the Tsutenkaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.47,0:26:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?! Why would he be at the Tsutenkaku?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.15,0:26:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn! We can't make it to the Tsutenkaku in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.82,0:26:35.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait for the Kid here!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.32,0:26:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Where's the egg right now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.57,0:26:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori apparently took it to a different location.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.91,0:26:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.00,0:26:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next up is...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.97,0:27:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A blackout?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.56,0:27:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?! What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.48,0:27:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's not right about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.57,0:27:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! A drink in the moonlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.61,0:27:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is even more elegant!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.87,0:27:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay calm! Switch to the private generator at once! Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.62,0:27:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.66,0:27:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know what he's after!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.05,0:27:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.47,0:27:42.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hoenzaka Mikado Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.51,0:27:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Dojima Century Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.85,0:27:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tenman Emergency Medical Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.52,0:27:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Chanel Ten Hotel.\NThe Naniwa TMS Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.56,0:27:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kansai World Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.27,0:27:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.12,0:28:12.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Move! How'm I supposed to turn right?!\N- Through-traffic gets the right-of-way!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.21,0:28:22.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He found out the real egg had been moved to another location!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.17,0:28:26.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So he blacked out the whole town to make them switch to a generator
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.10,0:28:28.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so he could locate them!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.06,0:28:32.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It'd be the only place besides hotels and hospitals with lights on!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.60,0:28:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kid! Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.62,0:28:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap! A dead-end!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.78,0:28:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hop on, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.54,0:28:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.58,0:28:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tsutenkaku'd be the perfect place to see where lights come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.04,0:29:03.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means he anticipated all this when he wrote his letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.59,0:29:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, to keep the hiding place less conspicuous...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.09,0:29:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...security would be light!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.56,0:29:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gonna get it if we don't hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.57,0:29:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.12,0:29:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- You stay here!\N- What?! Hey! Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.34,0:29:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.55,0:29:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.14,0:29:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.40,0:30:09.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.33,0:30:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hang gliders fly best with light headwinds!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.09,0:30:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning he's flying upwind, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.56,0:30:41.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's starting to lower his altitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.11,0:30:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Osaka Bay is up ahead!\NThe Kid's definitely gonna land!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.16,0:30:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori! You okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.25,0:30:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What're you doin'?! Get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.00,0:31:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let 'im get away and I'll kick your ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.08,0:31:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.38,0:31:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.84,0:31:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Call the police and an ambulance!\N- Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.76,0:31:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just hold on, Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.04,0:31:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.47,0:31:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This injury...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.89,0:32:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The egg's alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.73,0:32:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the Kid's monocle!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.94,0:32:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he get shot and fall into the ocean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.74,0:32:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In which case, who was that man just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.12,0:32:20.29,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That night, despite their exhaustive search efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.29,0:32:23.17,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the police couldn't tell if the Kid survived or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.75,0:32:30.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The next day, to ascertain if the egg was undamaged,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.01,0:32:33.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}its display was canceled, and it was to be taken back to Tokyo
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.05,0:32:35.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}aboard a Suzuki family ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.32,0:32:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My great-grandfather's name was Kiichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.20,0:32:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He worked as a craftsman at Fabergé's workshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.83,0:33:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He married a Russian woman there,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.54,0:33:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the year after the revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.00,0:33:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they returned to Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.79,0:33:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,where my great-grandmother had a baby girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.21,0:33:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my great-grandmother died shortly after, and 9 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.55,0:33:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,my great-grandfather also passed away, at the young age of 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.88,0:33:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this baby would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.01,0:33:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.02,0:33:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandfather and my parents died in an accident when I was five,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.56,0:33:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I was raised by my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.98,0:33:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She passed away this past month.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.99,0:33:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was working as a pastry chef in Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.74,0:33:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I returned here to tend to her personal belongings,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.58,0:33:45.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I found this old drawing\NI think my great-grandfather did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.00,0:33:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The middle is torn out, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.42,0:33:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.84,0:33:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it is the Memories Egg.\NBut this one has jewels on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.72,0:34:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it had jewels originally, but they got taken at some point?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.39,0:34:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say. Could there have been two eggs, actually?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.19,0:34:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.11,0:34:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, look. The contours are too different to be only one egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.90,0:34:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was actually a bigger piece of paper with two drawn on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.49,0:34:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but a huge part in the middle is missing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.95,0:34:25.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.95,0:34:30.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why is it "Memories"?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.38,0:34:32.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a mirror here...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.80,0:34:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops! It came out!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.47,0:34:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.80,0:34:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a mirror in it, but it came out...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.10,0:34:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.01,0:34:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.31,0:34:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's okay! That mirror's made to come out easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.44,0:34:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it was added afterwards or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.07,0:34:56.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? There's an image of something!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.57,0:34:58.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.20,0:35:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Turn off the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.16,0:35:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.28,0:35:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you! What do you think you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.68,0:35:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How is there a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.85,0:35:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- It's a "Magic Mirror."\N- Magic Mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.76,0:35:27.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard of those!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.47,0:35:31.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're from Japan and China, where people worshipped mirrors!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.15,0:35:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. They're specially-crafted mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.07,0:35:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say covert Christians in\NJapan secretly prayed to crosses
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.07,0:35:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that they projected onto walls using them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.07,0:35:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sawabe{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is this castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.87,0:35:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Without question, it is the Yokosuka Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.45,0:35:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yokosuka Castle? The one often used for commercials and such?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.00,0:35:56.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. My great-grandfather was the one who built it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.42,0:35:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandmother looked after it all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.13,0:36:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that was a Kosaka family castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.05,0:36:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, could your great-grandfather have made the two eggs?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.31,0:36:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the Russian Revolution, your great-grandfather and his wife
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.15,0:36:19.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,returned to Japan with the two eggs he made.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.03,0:36:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He likely sold many of the jewels on this second egg,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.07,0:36:29.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,built a castle in Yokosuka, and hid the egg somewhere inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.62,0:36:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then he left a message saying that he hid it inside the castle
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.63,0:36:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in a Magic Mirror in another egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.25,0:36:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I also found this old key with the drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.09,0:36:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it mean something, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.59,0:36:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no question that that key is for the second egg's hiding spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.56,0:36:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mysterious egg, encrusted with jewels...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.39,0:36:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's found, it'd be worth over 1 billion... no, 1.5 billion!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.23,0:37:02.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is that why the Kid went after it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.61,0:37:04.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.78,0:37:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.70,0:37:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you accompany me to the castle when we arrive at Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.03,0:37:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.66,0:37:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Please allow me to come, as well.\N- Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.46,0:37:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Yeah! Lemme get it on film!\N- I'd love to come, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.92,0:37:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure! We can all go together!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.17,0:37:23.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What the... Everyone's got a new look in their eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.30,0:37:26.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Are they going after the second egg too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.02,0:37:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- There we go.\N- Good bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.11,0:37:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! I stopped the bleeding!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.61,0:37:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As long as we keep the wound wrapped, it'll fly again!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.24,0:37:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?! That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.70,0:37:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Luckily, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} only suffered some light sprains,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.58,0:37:53.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but do you suppose the Kid is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.04,0:37:56.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He would never die like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.00,0:37:58.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who knows, maybe he's already on this ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.09,0:38:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.59,0:38:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a great expression! Thanks for the shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.68,0:38:15.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.27,0:38:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hi, Ran! We came to visit!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.06,0:38:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, too! Come on in!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.11,0:38:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to disturb you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.07,0:38:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.45,0:38:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I'll pass, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.12,0:38:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.20,0:38:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it! He's embarrassed being around so many beautiful girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.08,0:38:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.21,0:38:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot the other beautiful girl!\NI'll go get her!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.13,0:38:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.05,0:38:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Let's go, Squirt!\N- I'm coming too?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.22,0:38:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.93,0:38:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be ready soon. Just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.89,0:38:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Grigorii..."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.06,0:39:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Is that a photo of your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.23,0:39:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.52,0:39:07.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's got a man. They're so lucky...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.15,0:39:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I totally should've gotten my hands on the Kid when I had the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.11,0:39:14.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you could get him, the police wouldn't be having so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.87,0:39:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you lived in Paris since you were 20, Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.38,0:39:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NSo sometimes I use strange Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.71,0:39:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of strange Japanese,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.47,0:39:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there's a phrase I heard as a child and never forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.39,0:39:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.14,0:39:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Barushe niku katta be ka?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.27,0:39:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.56,0:39:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it means, "Did Barougier buy meat?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.48,0:39:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't know whose name that could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.40,0:39:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your eyes are...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.41,0:39:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep! They're gray! The same as my mother and grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.12,0:39:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think we got it from my great-grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.41,0:40:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, your eyes are gray too, Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.25,0:40:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they are! Do Chinese people have gray eyes, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.96,0:40:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, "Seiran" is written as "blue orchid," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.39,0:40:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name means "orchid," too!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.47,0:40:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Seiran" is the Japanese reading.\NIt's really "Chinran."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.48,0:40:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chinran?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.60,0:40:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sei" is "Chin," "Ran" is "Ran."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.35,0:40:27.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hoshi" is "Pusu," so it's Pusu Chinran.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.48,0:40:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So "Ran" is pronounced "Ran" in Chinese, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.40,0:40:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. "Mouri" would be "Maori."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.41,0:40:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So my name would be Maori Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.58,0:40:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like how cute that sounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.62,0:40:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh! How about me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.16,0:40:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suzuki Sonoko would be "Lingmu Yuanzi."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.62,0:40:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Lingmu Yuanzi...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.96,0:40:52.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, I think we may be about the same age, Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.17,0:40:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.47,0:40:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it! What month?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.47,0:40:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May. May 5th.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.68,0:41:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?! I'm May 3rd! We're only two days apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.81,0:41:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, then you're both one day apart from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.82,0:41:11.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}One day apart? That would mean May 4th...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.99,0:41:14.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's the same as Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.49,0:41:19.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's a big coincidence... Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.04,0:41:23.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could Conan{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-kun{\r\be10} actually be...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.51,0:41:35.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's so dumb. That couldn't possibly be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.89,0:41:43.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's what I get for obsessing about him. I really am dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.53,0:41:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.53,0:42:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!\NWhy don't you join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.70,0:42:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- You don't mind?\N-No, be my guest!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.26,0:42:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! You're so nice and sexy!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.47,0:42:18.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This old man's a lost cause...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.55,0:42:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.35,0:42:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.39,0:42:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! That pendant!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.31,0:42:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? I'm impressed. You're definitely a Romanov Dynasty researcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.48,0:42:32.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanna look?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.73,0:42:36.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? Was he always wearing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.74,0:42:41.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Maria"?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.58,0:42:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the ring of Maria,\NNicholai II's third daughter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.50,0:42:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so, if that's what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.17,0:42:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did you get it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.01,0:42:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think it's real?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.09,0:43:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I would need to do a more detailed check.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.68,0:43:06.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.\NYour pen's about to fall out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.27,0:43:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.65,0:43:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Are you there, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.82,0:43:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, dinner finally ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.36,0:44:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's terrible! Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is...\NSagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is dead in his room!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.53,0:44:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.04,0:44:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.01,0:44:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was shot in the right eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.72,0:44:27.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Kid was shot in the right eye, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.89,0:44:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you! Butt out, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.77,0:44:34.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.19,0:44:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His cheeks are just starting to stiffen.\NIt's been less than 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.74,0:44:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His ring pendant is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.62,0:44:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chairman Suzuki! This was a murder!\NContact the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.08,0:44:53.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.67,0:44:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.30,0:45:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.05,0:45:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.72,0:45:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you going on vacation to Karuizawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.47,0:45:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I find cabin life boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.89,0:45:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Did something happen?\N- Perfect timing. Come with us, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.79,0:45:33.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector! We've been expecting you!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.71,0:45:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly! Why do incidents always happen wherever you go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.83,0:45:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose it's a message from God?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.84,0:45:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you're not the god, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.34,0:45:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The god of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.22,0:45:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Assistant Inspector Shiratori is harsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.48,0:45:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's with that bandage?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.27,0:46:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, uhh, I had a bit of a scuffle with a criminal yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.74,0:46:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was Sagawa Ryu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 32. A freelance filmographer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.95,0:46:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector! This was a murder-robbery!\NThe killer stole a ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.25,0:46:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.29,0:46:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! It originally belonged to Maria, third daughter of Nicholai II!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.79,0:46:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had it on a pendant he wore around his neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.50,0:46:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was about the ring, the person could've just taken the pendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.59,0:46:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.64,0:46:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...not only is the room in shambles, but even the pillow's been cut open!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.72,0:46:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you scampering around again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.97,0:46:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure! This was on the floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.31,0:46:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pen, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.73,0:46:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"M. Nishino"?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.73,0:46:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is definitely your pen, correct, Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.70,0:46:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes. But what was it doing in Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.83,0:46:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who found his body, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.99,0:46:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Dinner was ready, so I went to get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.00,0:47:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Did you enter the room then?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.34,0:47:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why was your pen in his room if you hadn't gone inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.63,0:47:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.84,0:47:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what were you doing at around 7:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.68,0:47:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... I was in my room, taking a shower at about 7:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.85,0:47:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I took a short break after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.43,0:47:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Daddy, you don't think Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.02,0:47:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. I don't think he would.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.69,0:47:27.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If Nishino{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} did kill Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.78,0:47:31.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}then it's possible he's the one who shot the Kid, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.87,0:47:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.87,0:47:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've found that all the victim's videotapes are gone from his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.87,0:47:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- What?!\N- I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.71,0:47:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the room was ransacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.21,0:47:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it, Conan! Quit running around!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.75,0:47:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay. I'll get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.15,0:48:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the killer could be wandering around with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.24,0:48:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please return to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.62,0:48:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.41,0:48:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll bring him back myself. Go on, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.08,0:48:22.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Umm...\N- Please let me handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.63,0:48:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Doc? It's me. I need you to look up something right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.84,0:48:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? A sniper who shoots right eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.43,0:48:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it. I'll look into it.\NCall back in 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.11,0:48:50.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}10 minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.04,0:49:00.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just my imagination?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.00,0:49:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.46,0:49:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked the ICPO's criminal database
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.13,0:49:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a criminal with unknown age and gender popped up!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.51,0:49:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's known as the Scorpion!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.30,0:49:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Scorpion?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.36,0:49:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector! I found it!\NIt was under Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.57,0:49:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.49,0:49:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems we have conclusive evidence now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.07,0:49:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, wait! I didn't do it, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.87,0:49:45.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're not the killer, then why did you have the ring?!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.00,0:49:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.38,0:49:50.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's almost for certain that the Scorpion is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.46,0:49:55.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which would mean\NNishino{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} is the Scorpion...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.01,0:49:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.01,0:50:00.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A rice hull pillow...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.60,0:50:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.97,0:50:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say! Are you allergic to feathers, Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.44,0:50:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yes, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.19,0:50:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you can't be the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.07,0:50:12.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.28,0:50:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go ahead. Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.45,0:50:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.45,0:50:22.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room was filled with feathers!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.04,0:50:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer even cut up the feather pillow!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.91,0:50:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone allergic to feathers wouldn't have done that!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.92,0:50:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you really allergic to feathers?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.71,0:50:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I can vouch for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.21,0:50:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even just a feather or two will make him sneeze uncontrollably.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.39,0:50:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is why he doesn't use a feather pillow!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.01,0:50:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! So that's why he ran from\NRan's room! Because of the dove!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.15,0:50:52.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So who is the killer, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.23,0:50:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, have you heard of the Scorpion?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.23,0:50:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Scorpion?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.78,0:51:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bad guy who goes to lots of different countries and always shoots
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.78,0:51:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,people's right eyes and kills them to get Romanov Dynasty treasures!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.24,0:51:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.87,0:51:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there was someone like that on the international wanted list.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.46,0:51:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?! Does that mean our killer here...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.92,0:51:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe it's this Scorpion.\NHe probably shot the Kid, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.18,0:51:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.26,0:51:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kid's monocle was cracked, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.05,0:51:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Scorpion shot the Kid down trying to steal the egg from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.10,0:51:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how do you know about the Scorpion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.02,0:51:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- No, I, uhh...\N- Dr. Agasa told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.24,0:51:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.28,0:51:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.28,0:51:43.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.49,0:51:48.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So it was Detective Shiratori I sensed watching me during that call!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.29,0:51:53.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Your secret will come to light!"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.08,0:51:56.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was that referring to Detective Shiratori?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.05,0:52:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if the Scorpion is the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.14,0:52:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why'd he steal Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s ring and hide it in Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.14,0:52:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.52,0:52:16.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn. I can't use the stun-gun wristwatch in front of Det. Shiratori.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.19,0:52:17.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.65,0:52:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, you and Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} knew each other, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.65,0:52:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.24,0:52:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was shocked when he saw you at the gallery yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.95,0:52:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.16,0:52:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You traveled all over the world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.17,0:52:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must've met him somewhere, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.67,0:52:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.97,0:52:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! It happened when I was touring Asia three years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.68,0:52:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was filming a little girl whose house burned down in a civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.35,0:52:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He refused to stop when I told him to, so I punched him unthinkingly!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.27,0:52:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must've held a grudge against you, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.02,0:53:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it! Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! You're the Scorpion!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.28,0:53:04.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.41,0:53:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, the feather thing already proved it wasn't him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.91,0:53:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.79,0:53:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you really lucked out, Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.16,0:53:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.67,0:53:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, had the Scorpion not killed Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.96,0:53:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you would've been framed as the ring thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.38,0:53:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hold on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.22,0:53:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.34,0:53:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like the two eggs, there are two overlapping incidents here!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.23,0:53:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two incidents?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.19,0:53:35.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now you got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.98,0:53:41.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the first incident,\NSagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tried to frame Nishino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.40,0:53:45.78,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In order to frame\NNishino{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} as the ring thief,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.78,0:53:48.74,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} showed the ring off to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.74,0:53:51.41,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, while Nishino{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} was showering,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.41,0:53:57.12,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}he snuck into his room and hid his own ring under the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.12,0:54:05.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then he took the pen.\NAll to make Nishino{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} look like the thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.09,0:54:08.97,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}However, that's when the second incident took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.97,0:54:15.35,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} was shot to death by the Scorpion.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.35,0:54:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Scorpion was most likely after the ring
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.35,0:54:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a tape that revealed his identity somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.44,0:54:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the ring hanging from his neck was gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.78,0:54:30.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the Scorpion ransacked the room in search of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.28,0:54:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, old man! That's amazing logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.00,0:54:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me, this is child's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.00,0:54:42.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the Scorpion is still lurking on this ship somewhere?!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.46,0:54:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that... an emergency life raft is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.97,0:54:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.47,0:54:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the Scorpion escaped in that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.55,0:54:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put out an emergency APB, but I believe finding him may be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.06,0:54:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Slipped right through our fingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.48,0:55:01.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did the Scorpion really escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.11,0:55:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any event, it's a relief to know the murderer is no longer on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.58,0:55:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.49,0:55:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Very relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.62,0:55:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's still a chance the Scorpion will appear
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.29,0:55:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at the Kosaka family castle for the other egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.84,0:55:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.34,0:55:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he may be headed there already.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.43,0:55:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure, as soon as we arrive in Tokyo tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.35,0:55:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to go to the castle with Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.27,0:55:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood. Do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.27,0:55:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You heard him!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.02,0:55:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're absolutely not coming along this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.36,0:55:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. Let's take Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.94,0:55:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.28,0:55:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His unique ideas could prove useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.70,0:55:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.28,0:55:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.09,0:56:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That dumb Conan makes me so mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.93,0:56:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! He doesn't contact us even once after going to Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.30,0:56:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He doesn't realize he's a member of the Junior Detective League!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.39,0:56:24.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor, have you still not found your driver's license?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.36,0:56:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know I put it around here somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.11,0:56:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s going to beat us there if we don't hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.74,0:56:43.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so good at finding things, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.00,0:56:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would seem I've found another bit of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.59,0:56:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Eh?\N- Tada!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.60,0:57:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, do you think\NSagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s ring really belonged to Maria?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.15,0:57:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno. Inspector Megure took it in to have it looked at, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.70,0:57:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Supposedly, Maria was the kindest of the four sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.45,0:57:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and had large, gray eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.87,0:57:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gray eyes? That's just like\NNatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.00,0:57:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe you know that the entire imperial family was shot to death
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.25,0:57:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after the Russian Revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.47,0:57:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the bodies of Maria and the crown prince were never identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.18,0:57:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.18,0:58:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's such a pretty castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.35,0:58:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's similar to the\NNeuschwanstein Castle in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.23,0:58:32.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's said that it was the model for the Cinderella Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.40,0:58:37.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? Come to think of it, why is it a German-style castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.53,0:58:40.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s great-grandmother was Russian...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.12,0:58:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yo! Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.71,0:58:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.09,0:58:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- How are you?\N- Doc! Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.38,0:59:00.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got a call from Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.\NSo I dropped by while on a drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.72,0:59:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. I upgraded them just like you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.64,0:59:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.73,0:59:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why'd you hafta bring them?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.56,0:59:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They snuck into the car while I wasn't watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.44,0:59:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is almost like right out of a fairytale!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.49,0:59:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The treasure must be hidden inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.86,0:59:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder how many boxed eel lunches it could buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.99,0:59:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen, you!\NYou're absolutely not allowed inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.54,0:59:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Yes!\N- We know!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.58,0:59:31.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, geez. They're being a little too well-behaved.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.54,0:59:33.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.29,0:59:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He said he had to drop by somewhere along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.51,0:59:49.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that!\NTook me a while to get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.48,0:59:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with the bag?\NAre you going exploring or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.82,0:59:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like they say, "You can never be too prepared."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.36,1:00:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd best be careful. The Scorpion could be closer than you think.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.16,1:00:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.80,1:00:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Please lock the door.\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.72,1:00:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- To keep the kids out.\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.48,1:00:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Alright! Let's go, too!\N- What are you planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.53,1:00:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're gonna find the treasure first!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.57,1:00:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There must be another entrance! Let's find it!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.61,1:00:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.00,1:00:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the Room of Knights.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.71,1:00:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's decorated with Western suits of armor and tapestries.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.84,1:01:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the Noble Women's Room.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.05,1:01:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The late mistress often spent much time in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.85,1:01:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said this was the most comfortable room.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.69,1:01:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the Emperor's Room.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.19,1:01:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say. I need to use the restroom...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.27,1:01:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The restroom is in the hallway, the furthest room on your right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.39,1:01:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.75,1:02:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't look like the egg is here, but that's okay!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.35,1:02:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What in the world?!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.19,1:02:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a security device\NKiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} built 80 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.19,1:02:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many such traps planted throughout the castle,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.99,1:02:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so please be careful.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.91,1:02:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, trying to beat everyone to it is forbidden, Inui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.66,1:02:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A flashlight should be the only tool you need.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.71,1:03:04.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} sure loved his contraptions. Which means...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.63,1:03:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say. Does this castle have a basement?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.88,1:03:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.55,1:03:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where on the first floor is the great-grandfather's room?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.30,1:03:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that would be his office.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.02,1:03:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.15,1:03:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Photographs of Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} and daily scenes from the time
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.82,1:03:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,are on display in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.00,1:03:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Where are the pictures of your great-grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.92,1:03:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, there aren't any.\NSo I don't know what she looked like.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.63,1:03:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's odd. There are all these pictures of Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, though...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.89,1:03:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Isn't this man Rasputin?!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.98,1:04:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's definitely him.\NThe signature even says "G. Rasputin."
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.81,1:04:06.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}G. Rasputin?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.86,1:04:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad. Who's Rasputin?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.15,1:04:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, uhh, all I know is he was one of the century's greatest villains...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.83,1:04:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was known as Rasputin, the Mad Monk.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.25,1:04:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He won favor with the imperial family,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.29,1:04:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then caused the downfall of the Romanov Dynasty.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.04,1:04:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He ruled as he saw fit for a short while,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.59,1:04:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but ultimately, Prince Yusupov, a relative of the emperor, killed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.05,1:04:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When his body was found in the river, his skull was caved in,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.89,1:04:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and one of his eyes had been... crushed, or so they say.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.18,1:04:42.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}One of his eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.90,1:04:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the other egg is more important than Rasputin right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.07,1:04:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, how are we supposed to find it in this huge house?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.54,1:05:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old man! Let me have that!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.00,1:05:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.87,1:05:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's wind coming from below!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.83,1:05:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a secret basement under here!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.13,1:05:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.05,1:05:11.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, given that Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} loved making contraptions,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.97,1:05:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there's gotta be a switch somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.35,1:05:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.85,1:05:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Russian alphabet!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.77,1:05:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That opens the door to the secret basement?!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.11,1:05:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think there's a password.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.32,1:05:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sergei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Try typing in Russian words!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.99,1:05:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.11,1:05:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be "memories"! "Vospominaniya!"
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.95,1:05:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Vospominaniya...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.91,1:05:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.04,1:05:47.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then try "Kiichi Kosaka"!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.83,1:05:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kiichi Kosaka...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.52,1:06:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing's happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.31,1:06:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, are there any words that were passed down to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.69,1:06:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.73,1:06:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Barushe niku katta be ka?"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.07,1:06:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.07,1:06:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That phrase you mentioned might actually be Russian!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.37,1:06:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Hey. What's he talking about?\N- Shh! Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.16,1:06:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, "Barushe..." what?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.37,1:06:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"...niku katta be ka?"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.92,1:06:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Barushe niku katta be ka?"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.96,1:06:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The spaces in the words might be different!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.38,1:06:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Baru sheni kukatta bekka..."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.80,1:06:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Barusheni..."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.34,1:06:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be "Volshebnick Consta Veka"?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.06,1:06:48.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Volshebnik Consta Veka!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.69,1:06:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.52,1:06:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In English, "The Last Wizard of the Century." In Japanese...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.61,1:06:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"...Seikimatsu no Majutsushi."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.99,1:07:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Last Wizard of the Century?\NWhy does that sound familiar?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.75,1:07:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kid's warning letter!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.96,1:07:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! Talk about a big coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.20,1:07:13.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Coincidence? Is it really?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.55,1:07:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, I'll try typing it in.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.59,1:07:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Volshebnik Consta Veka...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.64,1:07:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What's that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.91,1:07:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know about this!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.37,1:07:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well done, boy!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.89,1:08:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No luck! This one's locked, too!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.94,1:08:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Darn it! They're gonna beat us to the treasure if we don't hurry!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.61,1:08:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.98,1:08:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just going to check out that tower.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.24,1:08:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara! Is there something there?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.99,1:08:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- I bet there's treasure!\N- That would be great!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.79,1:08:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's open!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.62,1:08:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.96,1:08:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the deal, Haibara? There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.67,1:08:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never said there was anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.01,1:08:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! We should just give up and leave now!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.43,1:08:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.98,1:08:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.62,1:09:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hurt, you guys...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.66,1:09:13.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- You have a soft stomach!\N- It saved us from getting hurt!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.54,1:09:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.67,1:09:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Snake!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.72,1:09:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a snake. It's a rope ladder.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.85,1:09:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's rather old, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.56,1:09:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like it originally hung from up there, but snapped.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.98,1:09:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid thing, scaring us like that...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.98,1:09:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'll it be? Wait here for the Doc to rescue us?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.57,1:09:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or keep going forward?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.07,1:09:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- That goes...\N...without asking.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.74,1:09:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.41,1:09:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Still, Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...\N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.21,1:10:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was the password "The Last Wizard of the Century"?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.05,1:10:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think my great-grandfather might have been called that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.43,1:10:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was 16, he exhibited wind-up dolls at the 1900 Paris Expo,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.39,1:10:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then went to Russia after that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.23,1:10:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. 1900 truly was the end of the century.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.07,1:10:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It still keeps going?\NThis place is really far down...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.58,1:10:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.58,1:10:37.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- I heard a faint noise!\N- The Scorpion?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.37,1:10:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- I'll check it out!\N- Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.58,1:10:41.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.21,1:10:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please stay here with the others.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.76,1:10:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.57,1:11:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You?!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.75,1:11:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys?!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.83,1:11:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.13,1:11:22.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.46,1:11:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,? The thing that can attain your love in this world!?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.51,1:11:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.85,1:11:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come now, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! The more, the merrier!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.10,1:11:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.77,1:11:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,? The mystery begins to unravel!?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.61,1:11:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,? You still don't suspect a thing...?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.82,1:11:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- A dead-end!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.11,1:11:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did we take a wrong turn somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.86,1:11:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be. There was only one passageway.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.70,1:11:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means there's some kind of mechanism here, too...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.37,1:12:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! Look at all the birds!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.67,1:12:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's strange!\NThe big bird has two heads!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.80,1:12:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A double-headed eagle... An imperial crest.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.17,1:12:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.47,1:12:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that the sun behind the crown?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.64,1:12:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sun... Light?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.68,1:12:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.73,1:12:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Try putting a narrow beam of light on that crown!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.98,1:12:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.82,1:12:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It shined! What the...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.87,1:12:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone get back!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.59,1:12:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An entrance! Now I see...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.42,1:12:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a photometer in this crown.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.44,1:13:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.69,1:13:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a contraption...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.04,1:13:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like we're inside an egg...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.96,1:13:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.43,1:13:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears to be a coffin.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.85,1:13:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Western in design, but made of paulownia.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.89,1:13:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a huge lock, though...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.94,1:13:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! That key!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.86,1:13:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.99,1:13:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is what it opens...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.45,1:14:03.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means inside the coffin is...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.79,1:14:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- May I open it?\N- Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.38,1:14:12.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pretty heavy...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.59,1:14:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One corpse... and the egg.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.01,1:14:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as if the person's holding the egg while asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.02,1:14:25.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is this your great-grandfather?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.10,1:14:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. I think it might be great-grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.11,1:14:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My great-grandfather has a lone grave in Yokosuka,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.94,1:14:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which I always thought was strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.61,1:14:39.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that she couldn't be buried in the ancestral plot
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.62,1:14:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because she was Russian.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.08,1:14:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I know this is hardly the time, but may I see the egg?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.38,1:14:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.59,1:14:56.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.43,1:15:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a small hole in the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.02,1:15:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's empty inside?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.77,1:15:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.06,1:15:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does this mean?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.98,1:15:10.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.10,1:15:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that a matryoshka?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.23,1:15:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Eh?!\N- A matryoshka?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.61,1:15:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have one at home!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.07,1:15:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dad's friend bought us one as a souvenir from Russia!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.82,1:15:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's a matryo... shka?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.08,1:15:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Russian doll in which smaller and smaller dolls are placed inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.08,1:15:34.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it could be possible! Have a look!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.92,1:15:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears the notches inside are meant to keep the inner egg in place.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.80,1:15:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn! If only we had that egg, we could find out!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.81,1:15:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We do have the egg.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.10,1:15:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought this might happen, so I borrowed it from Chairman Suzuki.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.15,1:15:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now. You didn't borrow it without telling him, did you?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.78,1:16:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, come now.\NYou know I would never do that...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.20,1:16:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's test it out, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.62,1:16:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It fits perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.29,1:16:15.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't make two separate eggs,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.21,1:16:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he made the two eggs as one.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.30,1:16:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- You seem dissatisfied.\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.05,1:16:25.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't shake the feeling there's more to the eggs than just that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.97,1:16:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something worthy of the name "The Last Wizard of the Century..."
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.31,1:16:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are some incredible diamonds!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.48,1:16:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think they're diamonds.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.23,1:16:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.28,1:16:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think they might be ordinary glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.65,1:16:41.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Glass?!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.53,1:16:44.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait a minute! Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.99,1:16:47.66,Flashback Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The glass on the inside of the egg's lid...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.66,1:16:49.66,Flashback Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Flashback Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s room...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.66,1:16:52.87,Flashback Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The mechanism with the light...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.87,1:16:55.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And that pedestal!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.25,1:17:01.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It has to be! The pieces of glass in the eggs are meant to be lenses!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.01,1:17:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sergei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Let me see the egg!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.38,1:17:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not more of your...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.72,1:17:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.56,1:17:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I help somehow?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.39,1:17:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring your light!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.36,1:17:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Narrow the beam, and put it in the pedestal!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.77,1:17:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.69,1:17:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sergei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Put out the candles!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.53,1:17:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this all about?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.91,1:17:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.55,1:17:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can see inside the eggs!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.30,1:17:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The imperial family figure is rising without any winding-up!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.14,1:17:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a photometer inside the Egg.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.41,1:18:07.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What the...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.24,1:18:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-These are...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.29,1:18:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...photographs of\NEmperor Nicholai and his family!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.09,1:18:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! The figures inside the egg weren't looking at an ordinary book!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.30,1:18:28.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was an album!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.34,1:18:32.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why it's the "Memories Egg..."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.43,1:18:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had the imperial family survived to receive this,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.02,1:18:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,never would they have been given a greater present!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.15,1:18:49.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your great-grandfather truly was the last wizard of the century!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.16,1:18:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think my great-grandmother would be delighted to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.33,1:18:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.87,1:18:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that your great-grandfather in that photograph?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.17,1:19:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That one with two people sitting in a chair.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.13,1:19:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is! That must be my great-grandmother with him, then!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.97,1:19:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My great-grandmother... I finally get to see what she looks like...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.52,1:19:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must be the only photograph taken in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.35,1:19:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} must've added it in afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.86,1:19:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? She...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.16,1:19:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...looks just like Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.38,1:19:50.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems this egg is Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s... no, Japan's... treasured legacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.18,1:19:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Russia hereby forfeits the ownership rights of both eggs.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.72,1:19:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears they are worth their most in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.43,1:20:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.23,1:20:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the inner egg belongs to Chairman Suzuki...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.19,1:20:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll speak with Chairman Suzuki myself!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.53,1:20:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll understand!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.74,1:20:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Come to think of it, where'd Inui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.83,1:20:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rasputin.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.08,1:20:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't in any of the photographs,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.37,1:20:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even though he was close to the imperial family.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.62,1:20:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He was in a photo in Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.76,1:20:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Russian "G"! It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.39,1:20:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, all has ended well!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.39,1:20:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.97,1:20:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, then!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.48,1:20:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.94,1:20:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the big idea?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.73,1:20:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't pick it up, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.48,1:20:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.90,1:20:51.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.57,1:20:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone get down!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.58,1:21:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The egg!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.42,1:21:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dammit! You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.00,1:21:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.63,1:21:10.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! You take care of things here!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.59,1:21:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.97,1:21:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.50,1:21:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.46,1:21:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.56,1:22:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.29,1:22:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There has to be a switch to open it from the inside!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.33,1:22:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one spot is a different shape!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.11,1:22:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it right there!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.11,1:23:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're expecting too much if you think we'll just let you go!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.74,1:23:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know who you really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.37,1:23:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pretend to be Chinese, but you're really actually Russian.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.54,1:23:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.08,1:23:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...descendant of "Mad Monk" Rasputin...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.25,1:23:15.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.64,1:23:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What's this?! The path's sealed!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.27,1:23:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean we can't get out?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.48,1:23:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Follow me, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.15,1:23:32.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.73,1:23:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.11,1:23:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just do what I say!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.49,1:23:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.16,1:23:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize it at first.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.75,1:23:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That voice! Sagawa?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.50,1:23:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you rearrange your
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.67,1:23:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chinese name of "Pusu Chinran,"
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.05,1:23:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you get "Rasputin"!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.92,1:24:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I killed you!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.98,1:24:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Romanov Dynasty's treasures were supposed to go to Rasputin,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.94,1:24:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who shared a deep connection with the imperial family.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.98,1:24:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Convinced of that, you decided to gather all those treasures yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.95,1:24:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for your ancestor's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.82,1:24:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your insistence on shooting people in the right eye
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.45,1:24:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is to avenge your savagely-murdered ancestor, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.46,1:24:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Inui?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.55,1:24:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- I'm alone.\N- What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.18,1:24:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is called a voice-changing bowtie.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.81,1:24:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can produce all kinds of voices.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.68,1:24:51.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.98,1:24:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa Conan. A detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.86,1:25:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You killed Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} because your identity could've been revealed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.15,1:25:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he went to people's rooms and filmed them on tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.20,1:25:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It happened so quick that you forgot to turn the photo upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.83,1:25:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a photo of your lover.\NIt was of Grigorii Rasputin!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.75,1:25:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grigorii starts with a G, and looks like an upside-down L in Russian.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.22,1:25:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So his Russian signature on the photo in Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.51,1:25:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,didn't make the connection obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.39,1:25:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Convinced that Sagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} caught your Rasputin photo on video,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.56,1:25:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you went to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.11,1:25:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.03,1:25:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or should I say, Scorpion?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.28,1:25:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm impressed, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.87,1:25:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I take it you killed Inui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.79,1:25:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because he saw you attaching the silencer to that gun?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.04,1:25:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my. It's almost as if you saw it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.92,1:26:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you went after the old man because he insulted Rasputin.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.30,1:26:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad. Who's Rasputin?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.72,1:26:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, uhh, all I know is he was one of the century's greatest villains...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.73,1:26:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then you even tried to kill Ran...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.31,1:26:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough talk now.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.82,1:26:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a real shame, but now it's your time to die, too!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.20,1:26:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That gun's a Walther PPK/S, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.16,1:26:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It holds eight bullets per magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.83,1:26:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One each for Inui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the old man, and Ran, and the five just now...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.13,1:26:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're out of bullets.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.92,1:26:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's an interesting tidbit for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.09,1:26:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a bullet's already loaded when you insert an 8-bullet magazine,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.76,1:26:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you get 9 shots.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.31,1:26:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, there's one more bullet in this gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.15,1:27:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shoot, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.98,1:27:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there really is a bullet left.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.71,1:27:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Foolish little boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.13,1:27:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.72,1:27:39.73,Signs,,0,0,0,,I sadly watched the rain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.72,1:27:39.73,Signs,,0,0,0,,pound on you as you bent over
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.19,1:27:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too bad, Scorpion.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.19,1:27:44.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,I sadly watched the rain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.19,1:27:44.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,pound on you as you bent over
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.82,1:27:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the Doc to remodel these glasses with especially hard glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.36,1:27:59.16,Signs,,0,0,0,,I can't do anything, but I can't
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.36,1:27:59.16,Signs,,0,0,0,,get drenched in your place, either
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.91,1:27:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.37,1:27:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah! I guess!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.16,1:28:09.51,Signs,,0,0,0,,I beg of you, please confess your worries to me
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.33,1:28:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright! Let's get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.01,1:28:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.02,1:28:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm saved...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.03,1:28:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh no! The castle is on fire!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.25,1:28:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.93,1:28:55.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.22,1:28:58.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You dummy...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.81,1:29:01.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!\N- Conan!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.56,1:29:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Quit yelling.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.90,1:29:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.90,1:29:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Shiratori took this egg back from the Scorpion.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.90,1:29:15.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori did?!\NWhat happened to the Scorpion, then?!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.91,1:29:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He arrested the Scorpion, Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and took her away in his car.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.75,1:29:21.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.79,1:29:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the Scorpion?!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.92,1:29:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here! He told me to give it to you, Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.92,1:29:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.76,1:29:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe Seiran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the Scorpion.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.93,1:29:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had such beautiful legs...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.98,1:29:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'm sorry it turned out like this...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.82,1:29:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all! The castle may've burned down,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.49,1:29:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I still have this precious egg my great-grandfather made!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.66,1:30:00.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I think the basement will be safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.70,1:30:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Once everything has calmed down,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.79,1:30:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we'll bury your great-grandmother next to Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.17,1:30:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the Kid never showed up at all...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.97,1:30:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think maybe he really is dead?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.55,1:30:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. He's alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.74,1:30:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old guy's already asleep.\NHe seemed really exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.33,1:30:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I can't blame him. A lot happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.01,1:30:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.59,1:31:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for saving me at the castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.18,1:31:06.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were really cool then, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.64,1:31:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were just like Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.11,1:31:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were really just like Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.41,1:31:20.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.45,1:31:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you're different people, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.58,1:31:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're different, right...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.05,1:31:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.43,1:31:44.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't do it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.56,1:31:49.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Listen, Ran...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.07,1:31:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, I'm actually...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.07,1:32:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.07,1:32:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.07,1:32:07.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,I sensed it ever since that day
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.41,1:32:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that really you, Shin'ichi?!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.00,1:32:13.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Even if we're both far away,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.25,1:32:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of hello is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.83,1:32:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came to check on you after I heard you got caught in an incident...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.05,1:32:28.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,I'm sure these feelings will reach you
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.92,1:32:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This... can't be!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.64,1:32:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You dummy! What were you doing?\NWhy didn't you ever call?!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.14,1:32:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry 'bout that.\NIt's just case after case, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.10,1:32:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to leave again tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.85,1:32:41.49,Signs,,0,0,0,,I entrust this wish to the passing seasons
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.48,1:32:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here! I'll get you some dry clothes!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.49,1:32:51.08,Signs,,0,0,0,,Love is always a red song
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.29,1:32:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not so fast, Kaito Kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.08,1:32:55.09,Signs,,0,0,0,,It's painful
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.16,1:32:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had me completely fooled.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.29,1:32:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never suspected you were on the ship, disguised as Det. Shiratori.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.09,1:33:05.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,I shed a single tear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.47,1:33:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!\NYou did a great job this time!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.98,1:33:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What do you mean?\NI just got back from Karuizawa...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.03,1:33:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.32,1:33:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew something would happen on that ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.24,1:33:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't really sure of it, but I bugged the ship's phone line anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.75,1:33:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One other thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.04,1:33:38.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You tried to steal the egg so you could return it to Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.17,1:33:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,its true owner.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.34,1:33:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that Kosaka Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made it,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.38,1:33:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that he was known as "The Last Wizard of the Century."
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.18,1:33:51.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you used it in that letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.22,1:33:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Anything else you've realized?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.60,1:33:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean how Natsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s great-grandmother was Maria,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.61,1:34:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the third daughter of Emperor Nicholai II?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.78,1:34:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maria's body was never found.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.45,1:34:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} helped her flee to Japan
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.20,1:34:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,before she was shot and killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.08,1:34:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love blossomed between them, and they had a baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.71,1:34:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But immediately after, she passed away.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.05,1:34:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To protect Maria's body from the Russian revolutionary army,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.22,1:34:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kiichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sold her jewels and built a castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.26,1:34:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he chose a German-style castle rather than a Russian one
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.98,1:34:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because her mother,\NEmpress Alexandra, was German.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.82,1:34:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Maria and the egg were buried in the secret underground room.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.61,1:34:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in the other egg, he left a clue about the castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.08,1:34:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the hope that a descendant would find it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.67,1:35:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this way, all the mysteries are solved.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.25,1:35:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have one piece of advice for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.26,1:35:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are some mysteries in the world best left alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.47,1:35:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it might be best to leave this particular mystery a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.02,1:35:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, can you solve this mystery, great detective?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.48,1:35:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did I show up as Kudo Shin'ichi and help you, a dangerous foe?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.19,1:35:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.96,1:35:45.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't be stupid. That's no mystery at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.38,1:35:52.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You only helped me as thanks for tending to this guy. Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.31,1:38:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Urgh! Why didn't you stop him for me, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.40,1:38:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} said he'd come back again!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.20,1:38:58.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good! The next time I see him...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.58,1:39:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...I'm gonna do that to him!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.50,1:39:14.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I guess I can't turn back to normal for a while, then...
